<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/79487053-billy"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1521282404i/79487053._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/79487053-billy">Billy</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It begins where the final book of the Mallorean leaves off (fifth book of the second series), but apart from the first chapter, the rest of the book i<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It begins where the final book of the Mallorean leaves off (fifth book of the second series), but apart from the first chapter, the rest of the book is self-contained.<br /><br />It is much more enjoyable however if you have read the other ten books in the series (first Belgariad, then Mallorean).<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
