<div id="review_842168073" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/842168073" />
    <a title="Mirta Martin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28295980-mirta-martin"><img alt="Mirta Martin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1391350001p2/28295980.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/842168073?book_show_action=true">Feb 02, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mirta Martin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mirta Martin" href="/user/show/28295980-mirta-martin">Mirta Martin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer842168073" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15943618159826531499">This one as well as Polgara-book are written wonderfully by the Eddings-pair. You get to peek at the time before Garion and friends and even if the two books (Belgarath and Polgara) have some of the same &quot;scenes&quot; it only made me feel exited: &quot;I remember this from the other book!&quot; You can basically live some of the same events twise, by reading the two wonderful novels, but from a whole different perspective, making it still feel a totally different stories, which they are.<br/><br/>David and Leight Edding</span>
  <span id="freeText15943618159826531499" style="display:none">This one as well as Polgara-book are written wonderfully by the Eddings-pair. You get to peek at the time before Garion and friends and even if the two books (Belgarath and Polgara) have some of the same "scenes" it only made me feel exited: "I remember this from the other book!" You can basically live some of the same events twise, by reading the two wonderful novels, but from a whole different perspective, making it still feel a totally different stories, which they are.<br /><br />David and Leight Eddings have an amazing talent of telling a deep story with lovable characters even with a timeline of thousands of years. The plot is clear and you can live through all the centuries without feeling things going too fast, slow or complicated. This is fantasy on it´s best!</span>
  <a data-text-id="15943618159826531499" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


